1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO CRIME; INCREASING THE PENALTY FOR AGGRAVATED
3 BATTERY UPON A PEACE OFFICER.
4
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF NEW MEXICO:
6 SECTION 1. Section 30-22-25 NMSA 1978 (being Laws 1971,
7 Chapter 265, Section 5) is amended to read:
8 "30-22-25. AGGRAVATED BATTERY UPON A PEACE OFFICER.--
9 A. Aggravated battery upon a peace officer
10 consists of the unlawful touching or application of force to
11 the person of a peace officer with intent to injure that
12 peace officer while the officer is in the lawful discharge of
13 the officer's duties.
14 B. Whoever commits aggravated battery upon a peace
15 officer, inflicting an injury to the peace officer that is
16 not likely to cause death or great bodily harm, but does
17 cause painful temporary disfigurement or temporary loss or
18 impairment of the functions of any member or organ of the
19 body, is guilty of a fourth degree felony.
C. Whoever commits aggravated battery upon a peace
20
officer inflicting great bodily harm, or does so with a
21
deadly weapon or in any manner whereby great bodily harm or
22
death can be inflicted, is guilty of a second degree felony."
23
SECTION 2. EFFECTIVE DATE.--The effective date of the
24
provisions of this act is July 1, 2026.
